Sentence: Ses03F_script01_2_F000 [006.9026-009.7483]: Why did you invite her here?
Does that bother you?
Ses03F_script01_2_F001 [011.1850-015.8191]: She's been in New York for three-and-a-half years.
She don't just suddenly come and-
Ses03F_script01_2_M001 [015.3375-018.7450]: Well, maybe, maybe he just wanted to see her.
Ses03F_script01_2_F002 [018.2825-021.4083]: You don't travel seven hundred miles just to see.
Ses03F_script01_2_M002 [021.2186-031.1858]: What do you mean?
They lived next door to each other their entire lives.
Why shouldn't he want to see her?
Hey, don't look at me like that.
I don't know anymore than you do.
Ses03F_script01_2_F003 [031.3317-034.0753]: He's not going to marry her.
Ses03F_script01_2_M003 [033.5925-036.3080]: How do you know he's even thinking about it?
Ses03F_script01_2_F004 [035.4616-037.3442]: It's got that about it.
Ses03F_script01_2_F005 [040.6075-042.7145]: What's going on here, Joe?
Ses03F_script01_2_F006 [043.4004-047.9389]: She's not Larry's girl.
She knows that.
Ses03F_script01_2_M006 [047.3697-050.2592]: You can't read her mind.
Ses03F_script01_2_F007 [049.5295-055.3231]: Then why is she married?
Then why isn't she married?
She's been in New York and there's hundreds of single men there.
Ses03F_script01_2_F008 [055.4106-059.7302]: I'm sure hundreds of them asked her and told her that she's foolish, but no.
Ses03F_script01_2_M007 [062.2403-065.1005]: How do you know why she's waited?
Ses03F_script01_2_F010 [065.3924-068.8072]: Because she thinks like me, that's why.
Ses03F_script01_2_F011 [069.9017-076.9065]: She's faithful as a rock, don't you know.
In my worst moments I can think of her-
Ses03F_script01_2_F012 [077.8075-082.4175]: I think again, that I'm-I'm right.
Ses03F_script01_2_M008 [083.3475-087.6200]: Look, it's a nice day.
What are we arguing for?
Ses03F_script01_2_F013 [087.1275-095.5300]: Nobody in my house better ever dare-dare to challenge her faith.
Maybe strangers, but not his father, not his brother.
Ses03F_script01_2_M009 [094.0900-095.9200]: Calm yourself.
Ses03F_script01_2_F014 [095.5800-100.5600]: Because he's not coming back.
Then what do I got to live for?
I'll kill myself.
Ses03F_script01_2_M010 [100.2250-101.8700]: Calm yourself.
Ses03F_script01_2_F015 [100.5600-103.1100]: Don't, don't laugh at me, don't laugh at me.
Because why, when she came here and she slept in his room, the memorial broke into pieces.
Look at it, look at it, Joe.
All right.
Calm yourself.
Ses03F_script01_2_F017 [111.3200-115.9050]: You got to believe, believe with me because I can't stand all alone.
Just calm yourself.
Ses03F_script01_2_F018 [116.8200-118.5000]: No, you've got to believe.
You above all people have got to believe.
Ses03F_script01_2_M013 [121.6800-124.5400]: Why me, above all?
Ses03F_script01_2_M015 [127.9300-130.8225]: Why me above all?
Ses03F_script01_2_F020 [130.1700-132.6600]: You got to keep believing.
Ses03F_script01_2_M016 [132.6100-135.3700]: Look at you, you're shaking.
Ses03F_script01_2_F021 [135.2300-137.1600]: I can't help it.
Ses03F_script01_2_M017 [135.5300-137.6600]: What have I got to hide?
What the hell's the matter with you, Kate?
